### What this is

This is ESLint's configuration file — the JavaScript equivalent of flake8's settings. It tells ESLint exactly what rules to enforce when the pipeline runs `npm run lint`.

**`env` block**
Tells ESLint what global variables are available:
```
node: true    — allows Node.js globals like require, process, module
jest: true    — allows Jest globals like describe, test, expect, beforeEach
es2021: true  — allows modern JavaScript syntax